post_text:
On the lighter side..... Because we left school before the robotics season concluded, the kids did not do the annual robot breakdown and parts organization event. As a result, I came out to the school to get all the VEX IQ robots and parts, and clean out the kids’ travel crates, so I can take everything home to breakdown and organize while I watch Netflix.

After emptying the crates, I have a few awards to give out:

-Most minimalist crate -Only the robot. Marie Kondo would be proud =*Team Broggle*

- Most organized crate - everything sorted into internal bins and held together with rubber bands (my heart was happy) =*The Slingers*

-Crate that looked most like a post-apocalyptic -Mardi-Gras -war-zone extravaganza =*Natural Harvest*

Missing my teams and all my students so much!
-Ms. Klein

TEACH-NW is Hosting a Virtual Art Exhibition!

TEACH-NW cordially invite friends, students and family to join us for a virtual reception on June 4th from 3p-5p. These two galleries feature a large collection of artwork and music created by our very own TEACH-NW students in grades K-12. Parents, friends and family are encouraged to join, chat and celebrate our student's creativity in an immersive virtual environment.

You can connect to this exhibition on any device, however we recommend using a laptop or PC. You can connect on a mobile device, but the experience may not be as enjoyable. Even better if you have a Virtual Reality (VR) headset!

https://www.marcola.k12.or.us/teach-nw/2020-tnw-virtual-art-exhibition

Mohawk Community, Mohawk FFA has 17 members with market animals available for sale, 10 of which are 1st year members. The Lane County Youth Auction decided to not to do a sale this year. We have beef, swine, sheep, and goat for sale.

These students purchase and work with animals for the purposes of education. All of the value of learning how to care for and raise a quality product. They are improving their skills with hands on practice. Due to these challenging times, some of the usually buyers are unable to help, so we are reaching out to you. There are multiple ways to support!

If you are interested in purchasing meat or supporting FFA member projects please contact the advisor for information. Kelli Fisher 541-501-2881 THANK YOUR FOR CONTINUED SUPPORT. Please feel free to share this post.

Here are a few of our members and animals.

Graduation 2020 Information

Wednesday, June 3: Baccalaureate is at the Marcola Christian Church (92419 Marcola Rd.) from 7:00-7:30pm for graduates only. The brief service and blessing of the class will be followed by the senior slideshow and photos. Graduates should wear their caps and gowns. No families will be allowed inside in order to maintain a group size of 25 or less. RSVP required by June 1 to the school at 541-933-2512.

Saturday, June 6: The celebratory Graduation Parade will start at the Mohawk Valley Assembly of God (92027 Marcola Rd.) at 11:00 am and proceed to the school. Spectators are encouraged to line Marcola Road at a safe social distance to cheer for the graduates heading to and coming back from the school. NO SPECTATORS WILL BE ALLOWED ON SCHOOL GROUNDS. Graduation will be live streamed so everyone can see and hear the speeches and awarding of diplomas in a special drive-through graduation ceremony.

Check back here for the live stream links before the events on June 3rd and 6th.

post_text:
⭐️ [MSD/TNW] Share Your Talent! ⭐️

We invite you to join in our first ever virtual talent show! What is your special talent? Can you make something, can you play an instrument, sing, tumble, or share something completely your own?!

All talent submissions need to meet these guidelines:
- All videos should be submitted by May 18th at 12p.
- Any MSD student and employee is welcome to share their talent. Other family members may be in the video.
- All themes and attire must be school appropriate.
- If singing, explicit lyrics are not acceptable.
- No lip syncing. Let your voice shine!
- Ensure adequate lighting, clear audio, and appropriate volume.
- Any video that does not meet the guidelines will not be included in the presentation.

Voting will take place on the 25th and the top three winners for each grade level (K-5, 6-8, 9-12) with the most likes will earn a prize. All student videos will be shared and celebrated with our communities (FB/Website/Email).

May 18 - Deadline to submit videos
May 25 - Deadline to vote
June 1 - Winners announced

post_text:
Congratulations to VEX IQ Robotics Team 75571X -Supreme LV!

Winning the prestigious Design Award at State, this team qualified for the enormous VEX Worlds championship in Louisville, Kentucky!

Due to COVID-19, the Worlds Championship was cancelled, and we did not get to travel. After all of the fundraising and work, this was very disappointing.

On Saturday, April 25, VEX ran a virtual Worlds tournament. For this fantasy robotics tournament, VEX used past match results of all 2020 Worlds qualifiers to generate simulated results.

Our Mohawk team did great! In their division of 110 teams, our team finished 25th! They would have made it into division finals before being eliminated!

Of the 620 teams who qualified for VEX IQ Robotics Worlds, our team finished in position 72! That is fantastic!

Congratulations Brooke, Kalab, and Emiliano in your fantastic robotics season!

Hey Mustangs! Tuesday, April 21 beginning at 2:00 PM, teachers and staff from both the elementary and the high school will drive much Of the bus route.

Our goal is to be able to wave to as many of our students and families as we can. We miss our students very much, and we want you to know that you are in our thoughts and hearts every day!

If you live along the Drive and Wave route, please be on the look and listen so you can come outside and wave to us from a safe distance. If you have to travel to our Drive and Wave route, PLEASE maintain a proper social distance of 6-10 feet from any other families, or stay in your car. Your health and safety is very important.

See the attached rout map pictures. Know that there may be delays along the route, as we are in multiple cars, and will be driving slowly so we can see everyone.

We are excited to see you Tuesday afternoon!

post_text:
Due to COVID - 19, Changes have been made to the Oregon State VEX Robotics Tournament.

Gold Division has been cancelled, and will not travel this weekend. There may be opportunity to gather at a later date for Gold Division competition, but this has not been planned.

Platinum Division will compete, but on Saturday only. The tournament will most likely be held at West Salem HS.

Middle School EDR will compete, but on Saturday only. The tournament will most likely be held at West Salem HS.

Only one teacher / coach per school is allowed to attend. No family, friends, or fans are allowed to attend this event.

Our middle school field setters will not be attending.

If Platinum and Middle School need to cancel, invitations to Worlds will go out based upon Skills Score rankings.

This is disappointing, but the right thing to do.

As of right now, travel to Nationals is still GO.
Travel to Worlds is still GO.
This status could change.

For questions, talk to Ms. Klein, or Mr. DeGeorge

post_text:
Please Help!

Seeking Volunteers for the Mohawk Robotics Tournament! The tournament is coming up on Saturday, February 22, and we still don’t have enough volunteers for this huge event.

Experience or special knowledge is not necessary, all you need is an interest in helping, and a readiness to experience the fun world of competitive robotics!

Event volunteers are the heart and soul of VEX Robotics competitions. We rely on Referees to keep things fair, Emcees to keep things exciting, and Queuers to keep things on schedule! Volunteering at a VEX competition is easy to learn, fun to do, and rewarding for everyone involved.

All training is provided via training videos ahead of the tournament (for referees), and experienced people will help on the day of. You’ll even receive delicious meals to keep your energy up!

Use the form below to volunteer! Thank you for helping our local youth in their endeavors!

Renee Klein
Dustin DeGeorge
Coaches

https://forms.gle/xBiphLrSPQTTRPT59

post_text: Mark Twain once famously wrote: “Travel is fatal to prejudice, bigotry, and narrow-mindedness..." That's right: Travel is a great form of education. So, send your student (and yourself!) to Costa Rica with us next spring break! Enjoy hot springs, snorkeling, and the excitement of getting to know a new culture. Mustangs have traveled to Europe, the East Coast, the Midwest, Alaska, and now we're off to Central America. For more info, join us in Ms. Lowry's room on Thursday at 5:30 or email her at llowry@marcola.k12.or.us. The world awaits!

post_text: On Tuesday Mohawk FFA spent the day at the State Capitol. Truly learning by doing! We watched the Senate and the House of Representatives in session. So proud of how well they presented our school and our community! It was genuinely impressive!

ATTENTION PARENTS OF MIDDLE SCHOOL AND ELEMENTARY ROBOTICS STUDENTS:

VEX IQ State is THIS SATURDAY, and we are still planning on going. All of our teams have qualified.

This is THE ONLY opportunity to qualify for VEX IQ Worlds, and is a very important event.

However, due to potential difficulty in getting the buses out of Marcola, parents may need to transport their own children to the State event, or arrange carpooling with other parents.

We will make arrangements for your children to get into the robotics lab to retrieve their robots, parts, and engineering notebooks, which they will need to take to the tournament.

I'm sorry about the inconvenience. I will let you know if things change regarding transportation.

Enclosed is a photo from Robot Events, showing the address and schedule for the tournament. I hope to see all competitors there!

Please email Ms. Klein for questions, or to let her know if your child will not be attending the State event.

Thank you so much for your support and flexibility!

Please email Ms. Klein with any questions!

post_text:
It's almost here! The Mohawk VEX IQ robotics tournament will be held THIS SATURDAY in the HS gym! This tournament is for our middle school and elementary school robotics teams. There will be a total of 20 teams competing, coming from several schools in Oregon.

Driver skills and programming skills start at 9:30.

The REAL action starts at 12:30 with qualifying rounds and finals!

Concessions will be available all day.

I am still in need of field re-setters for the day - if you have a child who would be interested in helping to re-set the competition fields in between matches, please let Ms. Klein know by filling out this form.

We also still need some help with judging. You do not need any experience with robotics to help with this position, and training will be provided the morning of the event.

To volunteer for this event, please complete this form. Ms. Klein will be in touch with you promptly!

https://goo.gl/forms/BZy0oUsnskMPY14H3

Thank you for supporting Mohawk Robotics!

See you on Saturday!

Attention all 5th and 6th Grade students! Join us May 20-22 for an outdoor learning adventure with the Coyote Outdoor School. This event is free for ALL 5th/6th grade Marcola and TEACH-NW students thanks to funding from the OSU Extension Outdoor School program and Measure 99 funding.

Due to funding requirements, this event is available only to students who have not previously participated in the Coyote Outdoor School program.

Coyote Outdoor School is the leading outdoor school provider in Lane County and the only Outdoor School recommended by Lane ESD. This three day, two night camp will be held at Camp Lutherwood in Cheshire, Oregon.

For more information about the Coyote Outdoor School program, please click here: http://bit.ly/CoyOutSch

TNW parents will be asked to drop off/pick up students on site. Marcola students will have bus services available.

After the deadline we will be in contact with parents on next steps for signing up. Please contact Anthony White (awhite@marcola.k12.or.us) for any questions.

http://bit.ly/TNWCOS

ROBOTICS NEWS!

Congratulations to team 98558R - Titanium Terror! Last night in West Salem they qualified to compete in Platinum level at state, as well as qualified for Nationals! This will be our first high school level robotics team to travel to Nationals in Iowa in April!

Congratulations to middle school level team 75571Y - The Cyclones! They have qualified for robotics state, and Nationals in Iowa, as well!

Information about how you can help these two hard-working teams travel to Nationals will be posted soon!

There was approximately 270 FFA members from 6 different high schools evaluating our most important agricultural resource SOIL! Special shout out to the Mohawk Alumni and Supporters for their hospitality. Jeff Litle for covering all the details and Jackson Gordon for doing the clean up. I know I'm leaving out our amazing students whom are the best helpers a teacher could ask for!

Come to The Roadhouse on Sunday, September 9 to support Mohawk Robotics!

They are having a 60'S Beach Bash with live music from Men From S.U.R.F. a Beach Boys / 60's cover band. The music and fun will be in the back yard and is an all ages, family friendly event. They will have picnic food for sale as well as their full regular menu and drinks.

The band plays from 5:00 PM - 7:00 PM.

The Roadhouse will be running a 50 / 50 raffle! The winner gets 50%, and the other 50% goes to Mohawk Robotics! Raffle tickets are only $1.00 each.

A huge thanks to The Roadhouse for this wonderful opportunity, and to the Marcola community for their continued support for our kids, programs, and our school!
